            . I <rs id="t18310908-321-viclabel1653" type="occupation">keep the Duke of York public-house</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-321-victim2318 t18310908-321-viclabel1653"></join>, Vauxhall-bridge-road: the prisoner was in my service - he had to receive money, and to account to me for it every night. On the 14th of July he asked leave to go out for an hour, and did not return; he was found in the street next day, tipsy, and this was discovered afterwards.</p>
               <p>
            
